docs.text: star wars : episode 1 - the phantom menace ( 1999 )
docs.label: positive

docs.text: review by matt pusateri
docs.label: positive

docs.text: few movies evoke nostalgia , enthusiasm , and affection like george lucas' 1977 classic , star wars .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the original blockbuster film and its two sequels not only evoked wonder and passion in a generation of filmgoers , but has deeply entrenched itself in american pop culture .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: arguably , more americans today can explain what " the force " or a " jedi " is than a budget deficit or a serb .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: so 22 years after the release of the original , and 16 years since the third film , the return of the jedi , how can any new star wars film withstand the weight of incomparable expectations and anticipation ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: can a new storyline and a new cast of characters possibly compete with the legends of the first trilogy - luke , han solo , and darth vader -all cultural icons ?
docs.label: positive

docs.text: against this challenge , the fourth star wars film , episode one : the phantom menace hit the screens last week .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and despite some early critical reviews in the major media , the film is neither a flop nor a disappointment .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: while the phantom menace is certainly not the finest film in the series , it is nonetheless engaging , exciting , and visually breathtaking .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it is a worthy sequel - er , prequel - to the original star wars films .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the phantom menace takes place decades before the setting of original films .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as the film opens , obi-wan kenobi ( ewan mcgregor ) , the wise old master who introduced luke to the force in the original star wars , is only a young jedi apprentice , still learning from his fellow jedi and instructor , qui-gon jinn ( liam neeson ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the republic government has sent the two jedi to settle a trade dispute that has developed into a blockade of the planet naboo by a shifty trade federation .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the jedi quickly find themselves not in negotiations , but in the middle of a planetary invasion , rushing to protect naboo's young queen amidala ( natalie portman ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: later , after eventually rescuing amidala and helping her escape naboo , they are forced to stop at tatooine to repair their battle-damaged ship before bringing her to the galactic senate to make an appeal for justice .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: on tatooine , qui-gon discovers a young slave boy , anakin skywalker ( jake lloyd ) , who not only can help them get the parts they need , but displays uncanny intelligence , insight , and instincts .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: qui-gon senses the child is " unusually strong " with the force and begins to suspect that he may be " the one " prophesized to " bring balance to the force . "
docs.label: positive

docs.text: as anyone who has watched the original star wars trilogy knows , far from being a galactic savior , the innocent-looking 9-year-old will in time become the ruthless darth vader .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: complicating matters further is a mysterious hooded figure , darth sidious , is behind the trade blockade and invasion of naboo , and sends out a lethal apprentice , darth maul , to find and capture queen amidala .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: while amidala and the jedi fight to save her planet , they soon also have to deal with the deadly and relentless darth maul .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: if the plot sounds a bit complicated , it is .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the phantom menace not only introduces an earlier generation of characters and an immediate crisis , but sets up the foundation for the events that will eventually lead to the fall of the republic , the demise of the jedi knights , anakin's turn to evil , and the rise of the dark empire of original trilogy .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but the complexity is not overwhelming .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the story moves quickly , with the only drawback being that many questions , predictably , remain unanswered at the end of the film , setting the stage for the next episode .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: one of the reasons the film's story seems hazy is not that it is too confusing , but too unfocused .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it's unclear whose story phantom menace is .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in the original trilogy , the movies were clearly luke's story , with the stories centering around his growth from farmboy to rebel hero to jedi knight .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but it's unclear whether this new film is anakin's story or obi-wan's .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: if this trilogy is centered on anakin , it's a shaky foundation .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: lloyd , like many child actors , lacks the subtle acting skills of adult performers , and as a result , his character seems shallow and unimpressive .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: on screen , we see nothing that suggests a dark side lurking underneath his little-boy face , or for that matter , any presence that would make him seem so special that qui-gon is willing to believe he is " the one . "
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the rest of the cast does fine , though they often work with some iffy dialogue by lucas .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: neeson is perfect as an aging jedi knight .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: mcgregor is well-cast as obi-wan and conveys a balance of youthful energy and calm sensibility .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: portman fits the role of a young queen well , but her lines were often very formal , giving her little room to give her character much personality .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the biggest problem with the phantom menace is not the plot or the characters , but the interaction between them .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: individually , the characters in this new film are no less developed than those in the original star wars , and the storyline is not more confusing than previous films in the series .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but unlike the previous trilogy , lucas doesn't do as good of a job playing the characters off one another .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in star wars , there were immediate contrasts and memorable exchanges between luke and han , han and obi-wan , and leia and luke .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the ensemble played off each other and immediately showed their distinct attitudes and personalities .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in the sequence in where luke , han , and chewbacca attempt to rescue leia from her cell on the death star , the audience learns a lot about all four characters in the ways they react to the immediate problems and each other .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: there is no comparable sequence in the phantom menace to flesh out the characters and their relationships with each other .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: individually , they are interesting characters with clear motivations and interests , but lucas develops little chemistry or tension between the them .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: this is perhaps the most glaring weakness of this film , and is probably the reason it has disappointed many reviewers .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but despite the need for a richer dialogue and stronger character interaction , the film is still very engaging .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: many of the wonderful elements of lucas' previous films make the phantom menace both memorable and entertaining .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: first , of course , is the remarkably rich and imaginative universe lucas creates .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the characters visit magical underwater cities , evade dinosaur-sized sea monsters , fight battle droids and menacing " destroyers " on venetian-looking planet of naboo , watch a spectacular event , part roman-chariot race , part nascar circuit , on the arid desert planet of tatooine , then head to corsucant , the gothic urban capital of the republic and home to the galactic senate and the jedi council .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: each location is elaborate and complex .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: lucas never settles for vague ideas about the look of his settings , he creates rich , spectacular landscapes , palaces , and skylines .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: most of the new special effects in his re-released special edition trilogy in 1997 were changes that allowed him to give the earlier movies the look and feel that just weren't possible when the films were made .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: more than ever , in this new film , lucas' universe is filled with a menagerie of creatures , robots with personalities , and a supporting cast of aliens who interact with the main characters .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the best such character is watto , a greedy tatooine junk dealer who owns anakin and his mother as slaves .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: watto has a scratchy italian voice and a short , paunchy body with oddly mismatched wings that flutter like a hummingbird as he floats around the room .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: of all the computer-generated characters in the film , watto is the best done and most enjoyable .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: speaking of computer-generated characters , no review of the phantom menace is complete without mentioning the most controversial figure in the film : jar jar binks .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: with more than 80 minutes of screen time , jar jar is the realization of george lucas' dream to include a fully computer-generated character into the cast of the new trilogy .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: jar jar , a clumsy amphibian and member of the gungan race , literally stumbles his way into the path of the jedi knights early in the film and becomes qui jon's accidental sidekick .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: jar jar usually performs a comic-relief role in the film , lightening scenes with his mishaps and inability to stay out of trouble .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the animation of jar jar is nearly seamless , and he interacts with the characters throughout the film as if he were really on the set with the actors .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: however , despite the technological magic that makes his character possible , jar jar isn't completely convincing .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: he still moves and sounds too much like a cartoon to blend into a scene .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: throughout the movie , jar jar never transcends a " roger rabbit " -like presence .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: you accept that he's there , but you never lose sight of the fact that he is an animated character .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: initially , i found jar jar annoying , but grew to enjoy the humor he added to the film .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: on my second viewing of the film , jar jar was a lot of fun and i didn't mind him at all .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: a second reason this film continues the fine tradition of star wars movies is that the film is replete with humor and small details that flesh out the world lucas creates .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: despite all the film's struggles between good and evil , and the sober musings about one's destiny and " the force , " like all star wars films , the phantom menace never takes itself too seriously .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: fortunately , lucas hasn't lost sight of the fact that his films are entertainment , not high art .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: from the bumbling jar jar , to a one-man , two-headed announcer team calling the action at the film's thrilling pod-race sequence , to a cameo appearance by e . t .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: in the film , the phantom menace is simply a lot of fun , with lots of half-hidden jokes and humor that can easily be missed .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and finally , the phantom menace works because , as in all his films , there is no shortage of speed and action .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: from beginning to end , there are light-saber battles , hair-raising chases , and thrilling duels between good and evil .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the pod-race sequence on tatooine is one of the most entertaining and exciting scenes in any star wars film , and the final showdown between obi-wan , qui-gon , and darth maul is arguably the best choreographed , most thrilling fight sequence lucas has filmed .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the phantom menace won't win any major oscars .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: it probably won't beat titanic's box office record .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and it's not even the best star wars film ( i'd put it third , after the original and the empire strikes back ) .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but it's an exciting and entertaining film , far better than your typical summer blockbuster .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the film can't live up to it's hype - no film , not even the original star wars , could have done that .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: but it's still worth seeing . . .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: probably more than once .
docs.label: positive
